{
  "texts": [
    "ResNet18 (He et al. 2016), a CNN trained on an ImageNet dataset, is used in this study.",
    "Temporal convolutional network (TCN) and various varieties of RNN namely LSTM, Bi-LSTM, and GRU are used as sequence-based models.",
    "It is implemented using MATLAB deep learning toolbox (TensorFlow 2023) on a system having 96GB RAM and NVIDIA V100 GPU, achieving an accuracy of 91.78%.",
    "Improved control over enhanced parallel processing capabilities and the receptive field size are the two benefits of using TCNs in this work.",
    "The main disadvantage is not being able to execute categorization and feature extraction simultaneously."
  ]
}